items.title: Alleged childcare paedophile Joshua Dale Brown hit with 83 new charges
items.standfirst: The 27-year-old is facing court over alleged sexual assault at childcare centres across Melbourne.
items.content: Accused Melbourne childcare paedophile Joshua Dale Brown has been hit with 83 additional charges after police identified four new alleged victims.The 27-year-old is now facing a total of 156 charges against 12 alleged child victims. Victoria Police said detectives charged him this morning with 83 alleged offences relating to four new children and the initial eight children.READ MORE: Experts caution against taking medical advice from influencersThe offences include 23 counts of using a carriage service to transmit child abuse material, eight counts of producing child abuse material for use through a carriage service, eight counts of sexual assault of a child under 16, and six counts of penetration of a child under 12. He was also charged with unrelated matters, including 12 counts of bestiality. The four new children had attended the Nino Early Learning Adventures in Point Cook on March 26 in 2019, Only About Children in Williamstown on December 1 in 2020 and February 22 in 2021 and Aussie Kindies Early Learning Centre in Keilor between February 3 and 11 this year.Their families have been notified and are receiving support services.Brown was initally charged with more than 70 offences relating to the alleged abuse of eight children at Creative Gardens Early Learning Centre in Point Cook in May.The charges triggered a mass health response that saw thousands of children get tested for sexually transmitted infections, with Brown having worked at 23 known childcare centres between January 2017 and May 2025.READ MORE: Second deadly mosquito-borne virus detected in daysHealth officials have confirmed that no children need to be tested again, as they have not identified any new childcare centres he had worked at.Detectives have continued investigating him after a magistrate granted them more time to gather evidence and pushed back the next court hearing to February 10.The investigation remains active and ongoing. Anyone with information is urged to come forward.Brown's alleged crimes have sparked statewide and national child safety and industry reforms.READ MORE: Ghislaine Maxwell's bold new bid to get out of prisonTotal list of Joshua Dale Brown's 83 new charges: Six counts of penetration of a child under 12Eight counts of producing child abuse material for use through a carriage serviceTwenty-three counts of using a carriage service to transmit child abuse materialSeven counts of using a carriage service to solicit child abuse materialSeven counts of using a carriage service to cause child abuse material to be transmitted to selfTwo counts of sexual activity in the presence of a child under 16Eight counts of sexual assault of a child under 16Two counts of attempted sexual penetration of a child under 12Two counts of recklessly causing injuryTwo counts of common law assaultTwelve counts of bestiality (these are part of a separate investigation and are unrelated to childcare centres)Reckless conduct endangering serious injuryEncouraging a child under the age of 16 to engage in sexual activityTwo counts of possessing a drug of dependenceNational Sexual Assault, Domestic Family Violence Counselling Service 1800RESPECT (1800 737 732).Kids Helpline 1800 55 1800.DOWNLOAD THE 9NEWS APP: Stay across all the latest in breaking news, sport, politics and the weather via our news app and get notifications sent straight to your smartphone. Available on the Apple App Store and Google Play.
